<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="135" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,847,1125]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1028,1053]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">Remarks</emphasis>
. On the basis of the description and location, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rahayu" box="[848,1094,1028,1053]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" refString="Rahayu, D. L. &amp; Ng, P. K. L. (2014) New genera and new species of Hexapodidae (Crustacea, Brachyura) from the Indo-West Pacific and east Atlantic. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 62, 396 - 483." type="journal article" year="2014">
Rahayu &amp; Ng (
<number box="[1027,1086,1028,1052]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" value="2014.0">2014</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
indicated that Tesch’s (
<number box="[1370,1428,1028,1052]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" value="1918.0">1918</number>
) records of “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Doflein, 1904" authorityName="Doflein" authorityYear="1904" box="[285,674,1063,1088]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hexapodidae" genus="Hexaplax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megalops">
<emphasis box="[285,507,1064,1088]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">Hexaplax megalops</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Doflein" box="[515,674,1063,1088]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" refString="Doflein, F. (1904) Brachyura. Wissenschaftliche Ergebnisseder Deutschen Tiefsee - Expedition auf dem Dampfer Valdivia 1898 - 1899, 6, i - xiv, 1 - 314, figs. 1 - 68, pls. 1 - 58." type="journal article" year="1904">
Doflein, 
<number box="[616,674,1064,1088]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" value="1904.0">1904</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
” from 
<collectingCountry box="[755,864,1063,1088]" name="Indonesia" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
probably belonged to their new species, 
<taxonomicName class="Malacostraca" family="Hexapodidae" genus="Hexaplax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurantium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">Hexaplax aurantium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Re-examination of these specimens confirms this.
</paragraph>
